Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

01:45.337 --> 01:47.771
(MUSIC CONTINUES)

01:52.592 --> 01:55.895
- sync and corrections by Caio -
- www.addic7ed.com -

01:57.070 --> 01:58.969
(WHISTLE BLOWS)

01:58.970 --> 02:01.537
(DOWN-TEMPO MUSIC PLAYS)

02:47.504 --> 02:50.370
(METAL CREAKS, STEAM HISSES)

02:51.670 --> 02:53.636
Don't go blaming yourself.

02:53.637 --> 02:56.035
It was my tonic she used, Doctor.

02:56.036 --> 02:57.902
But you weren't to know.

02:57.903 --> 02:59.504
Mixing it with...

03:01.303 --> 03:03.970
Oh, a prayer for her immortal soul.

03:16.036 --> 03:18.636
(WHISTLE BLOWS)

03:18.637 --> 03:21.370
(WHISTLE BLOWS, STEAM HISSES)

03:28.504 --> 03:31.035
ROY: Rest in peace, lass.

03:31.036 --> 03:32.470
JACK: Amen.

03:33.437 --> 03:34.936
SARAH: Amen.

03:35.837 --> 03:39.303
Oh, Mrs. Nordmann. A terrible tragedy.

03:42.303 --> 03:44.470
(MUSIC CONTINUES)

03:47.837 --> 03:49.302
Poor kiddies.

03:49.303 --> 03:52.303
Losing their beloved teacher like that.

03:52.737 --> 03:56.503
And her family, waiting for the coffin.

03:56.504 --> 03:58.369
For one so young to take her life.

03:58.370 --> 03:59.369
And then to use...

03:59.370 --> 04:00.770
If it hadn't been your mixture,

04:00.771 --> 04:02.770
she would have used something else.

04:02.771 --> 04:06.369
Some of my customers have
canceled their deliveries.

04:06.370 --> 04:08.369
Now, there's nothing
bodgy about your stuff.

04:08.370 --> 04:11.002
It's all been given the
all-clear, all right?

04:11.003 --> 04:12.370
Mm.

04:23.237 --> 04:25.637
(WHISTLE BLOWS)

04:35.704 --> 04:37.303
(HORSE NEIGHS)

04:40.737 --> 04:42.836
(BIRDS CHIRPING)

04:42.837 --> 04:44.902
Are you sure you'll cope without me?

04:44.903 --> 04:46.437
It's just till Monday.

04:47.570 --> 04:49.036
Good luck.

04:51.470 --> 04:53.837
(MID-TEMPO MUSIC PLAYING)

05:01.470 --> 05:03.903
ROY: Bloody awful way to go.

05:04.704 --> 05:07.036
Hard to get out of your mind.

05:09.036 --> 05:11.369
In here! In here! Quick!

05:11.370 --> 05:12.836
Quick! She's in here!

05:12.837 --> 05:13.970
Okay.

05:42.903 --> 05:45.636
(COW LOWS)

05:45.637 --> 05:47.537
(BELL CLANGS)

05:53.437 --> 05:54.871
Anna!

05:59.637 --> 06:01.969
Still working on your little book.

06:01.970 --> 06:03.102
What fun.

06:03.103 --> 06:05.202
How can we help you?

06:05.203 --> 06:06.636
There are things that need saying

06:06.637 --> 06:09.369
best said in your father's absence.

06:09.370 --> 06:10.836
Shall we say cocktail hour?

06:10.837 --> 06:13.771
- Oh, Regina, we'd really...
- No. I insist.

06:14.604 --> 06:16.903
No need to dress.

06:20.737 --> 06:21.736
Did I hear a "yes"?

06:21.737 --> 06:23.970
- Well, <i>she</i> obviously did.
- (GATE SQUEAKS)

06:25.370 --> 06:27.236
No, she's right.

06:27.237 --> 06:29.902
There <i>are</i> things that need to be said.

06:29.903 --> 06:33.436
(CHILDREN LAUGHING)

06:33.437 --> 06:35.336
(MUSIC CONTINUES)

06:35.337 --> 06:37.303
(HORSE SNORTS)

06:42.370 --> 06:44.303
(ENGINE SHUTS OFF)

06:44.470 --> 06:46.669
ROY: I'll pick you up
around 3:00, I suppose.

06:46.670 --> 06:48.302
Oh, I'll walk home.

06:48.303 --> 06:49.703
Thanks, Roy.

06:49.704 --> 06:51.637
(BELL CLANGING)

06:56.470 --> 06:57.770
Milly got away?

06:57.771 --> 06:59.369
Yes.

06:59.370 --> 07:00.935
You're a godsend.

07:00.936 --> 07:02.804
Looking after the lot
of them is a chore.

07:03.404 --> 07:04.836
How are you holding up?

07:04.837 --> 07:08.370
Well, I'm managing not to cry, just.

07:09.103 --> 07:10.570
If only I'd done more to help her.

07:12.837 --> 07:14.569
SARAH: And the children?

07:14.570 --> 07:17.002
Well, they do say kids are resilient.

07:17.003 --> 07:17.969
Yes.

07:17.970 --> 07:20.170
There's only one I'm worried about.

07:20.837 --> 07:22.503
Emma Carvolth.

07:22.504 --> 07:25.503
She's normally a bright
little thing, but she...

07:25.504 --> 07:27.236
Perhaps a-a nurse...

07:27.237 --> 07:29.236
I'll see what I can do.

07:29.237 --> 07:31.637
And if you need any help...

07:32.137 --> 07:34.302
I knew Milly was miserable.

07:34.303 --> 07:38.169
She and Gordon, her fiancé,
had some sort of...

07:38.170 --> 07:39.637
But...

07:40.837 --> 07:42.871
I should have seen.

07:45.103 --> 07:46.902
Class time.

07:46.903 --> 07:48.136
Yes. Into the fray.

07:48.137 --> 07:51.136
Don't let them get under your skin.

07:51.137 --> 07:52.302
Come on. (CLAPS HANDS)

07:52.303 --> 07:54.736
Come on. Let's go. Quick, quick.

07:54.737 --> 07:57.302
(DOWN-TEMPO MUSIC PLAYS)

07:57.303 --> 07:58.704
Hello.

08:01.670 --> 08:04.137
You're Emma. Am I right?

08:05.970 --> 08:07.803
I'm Mrs. Nordmann.

08:07.804 --> 08:11.137
I'm helping until the new
teacher comes on Monday.

08:13.237 --> 08:15.370
(GIRLS LAUGHING)

08:16.837 --> 08:18.770
(WHISPERING) I wonder
if you might tell me

08:18.771 --> 08:20.737
where my classroom is.

08:22.237 --> 08:23.536
Please.

08:23.537 --> 08:25.504
(MUSIC CONTINUES)

08:30.370 --> 08:33.437
So, how are you?

08:38.936 --> 08:41.602
ELIZABETH: Now, be
sure to send a wreath.

08:41.604 --> 08:43.236
It's important that the
girl's family know

08:43.236 --> 08:44.935
that others aren't being judgmental.

08:44.936 --> 08:45.902
It's done.

08:45.903 --> 08:47.570
Oh, thank you.

08:48.370 --> 08:50.935
Are the police sure it's suicide?

08:50.936 --> 08:53.536
There was some sort of rift
with her fiancé, apparently.

08:53.537 --> 08:56.370
He's with the Air Force in Malaya.

08:56.837 --> 08:58.036
How did she do it?

09:00.103 --> 09:02.169
Rat poison with a tonic.

09:02.170 --> 09:03.469
Her fellow teacher found her.

09:03.470 --> 09:05.270
It's dreadful.

09:07.437 --> 09:10.035
Puts our troubles into perspective.

09:10.036 --> 09:13.437
Limited comfort, under
the circumstances.

09:14.003 --> 09:18.504
Those came from Olivia, with this card.

09:21.903 --> 09:24.437
"Don't judge me too harshly."

09:25.437 --> 09:27.169
Have she and James spoken?

09:27.170 --> 09:29.636
They're meeting this morning, finally.

09:29.637 --> 09:32.102
I'm meeting him afterwards, Carolyn her.

09:32.103 --> 09:34.770
Well, don't waver.

09:34.771 --> 09:37.169
(DOWN-TEMPO MUSIC PLAYS)

09:37.170 --> 09:38.737
(PENCIL SCRATCHING)

09:40.537 --> 09:43.237
(HOOFBEATS, DOG BARKING IN DISTANCE)

09:44.737 --> 09:49.804
How can something society
condemns feel so perfect?

09:50.370 --> 09:53.136
Because society lives gray little lives

09:53.137 --> 09:54.436
devoid of any color.

09:54.437 --> 09:56.369
(CHUCKLES)

09:56.370 --> 09:59.403
That is such an artist's reply.

09:59.404 --> 10:01.837
That's the reply of a man in love.

10:10.437 --> 10:12.604
I should dress.

10:17.203 --> 10:19.369
- Shush, shush. It's all right.
- (BABY CRYING)

10:19.370 --> 10:20.636
There we go.

10:20.637 --> 10:22.170
All right.

10:22.237 --> 10:23.737
All right.

10:24.203 --> 10:25.836
Oh, wish me luck.

10:25.837 --> 10:29.736
Remember... you, me, Georgie, London.

10:29.737 --> 10:31.569
A whole new life.

10:31.570 --> 10:33.103
Remember this.

10:34.137 --> 10:35.569
Lloyd.

10:35.570 --> 10:37.936
Oh, who cares what anyone thinks?

10:39.036 --> 10:41.437
(BELL TOLLING IN DISTANCE)

10:43.337 --> 10:47.936
Sometimes, when things upset us,
it's good to write things down.

10:48.871 --> 10:51.503
So I would like to spend
the rest of today

10:51.504 --> 10:55.903
writing down how you feel about
what happened to Miss Davis.

10:56.470 --> 10:58.369
- Ow!
- (LAUGHTER)

10:58.370 --> 11:01.870
Now, you don't have to read
it out or show anyone.

11:01.871 --> 11:05.437
It's just for you... and me.

11:06.137 --> 11:08.437
And not even me, if you'd prefer.

11:09.370 --> 11:12.369
So you have half an hour.

11:12.370 --> 11:15.102
- (INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS)
- Quiet... Quietly.

11:15.103 --> 11:16.804
Quietly.

11:17.771 --> 11:19.536
Ow!

11:19.537 --> 11:21.170
Stop it, Larry!

11:21.704 --> 11:23.403
I think you need to stay behind.

11:23.404 --> 11:25.369
Stay behind what, Miss?

11:25.370 --> 11:26.770
(LAUGHTER)

11:26.771 --> 11:29.470
(DOWN-TEMPO MUSIC PLAYS)

11:37.570 --> 11:39.336
(CHILDREN SHOUTING IN DISTANCE)

11:39.337 --> 11:41.504
I'll, uh, I'll wait here.

11:43.303 --> 11:45.103
I'd kiss you if I could.

11:49.103 --> 11:50.771
Good luck.

11:59.036 --> 12:01.437
(MUSIC CONTINUES)

12:07.936 --> 12:09.837
(BABY COOING)

12:33.537 --> 12:35.303
No hope?

12:44.370 --> 12:45.737
No.

13:31.837 --> 13:33.303
(DOOR OPENS)

13:38.871 --> 13:42.537
I still like you, Miss, even
if you're keeping me in.

13:43.637 --> 13:45.637
Two more minutes.

13:50.637 --> 13:52.870
REGINA: I accept that
you've cast me in the role

13:52.871 --> 13:54.703
of wicked stepmother.

13:54.704 --> 13:58.069
But your father and I married
for his political career.

13:58.070 --> 14:01.369
I'm asking that you respect our
union for the same reason.

14:01.370 --> 14:03.637
You can't blame me for how I feel.

14:04.203 --> 14:05.804
Need we talk about blame?

14:06.936 --> 14:09.837
Please, a cease-fire.

14:10.404 --> 14:12.903
- For your father's sake.
- Not your own?

14:13.437 --> 14:14.935
Me? No.

14:14.936 --> 14:16.770
I simply wish to spare him the burden

14:16.771 --> 14:19.236
of a spoiled brat doing
what she's always done...

14:19.237 --> 14:20.836
assuming everything is about her.

14:20.837 --> 14:24.504
- Hey, hey...
- As I said, a frank discussion.

14:24.970 --> 14:27.636
I will not toady for
your approval, Anna.

14:27.637 --> 14:30.069
It will come in time or it will not.

14:30.070 --> 14:31.369
It will not.

14:31.370 --> 14:33.369
Regardless, I am asking for a truce.

14:33.370 --> 14:34.704
And if I don't give it?

14:37.637 --> 14:42.302
Please... don't make
me go to your father.

14:42.303 --> 14:44.337
How do you think he'll see your refusal?

14:45.871 --> 14:50.669
I imagine he'll see it as the
actions of a petulant child.

14:50.670 --> 14:51.902
Let's go, Anna.

14:51.903 --> 14:53.969
You could have said all that
without dragging us here.

14:53.970 --> 14:56.469
Some things are best said
on one's home ground,

14:56.470 --> 14:59.436
and this is now my home ground.

14:59.437 --> 15:01.070
Let yourselves out.

15:03.370 --> 15:07.003
And my little novel is
going to be published.

15:07.570 --> 15:09.370
Thank you for asking.

15:11.737 --> 15:13.369
- Why now?
- What do you mean?

15:13.370 --> 15:15.236
She's known my attitude
for quite some time,

15:15.237 --> 15:16.770
so why this now?

15:16.771 --> 15:19.771
Something's got her
building her defenses.

15:21.137 --> 15:22.404
Let's go.

15:24.570 --> 15:27.437
(VEHICLES PASSING, HORNS HONKING)

15:29.704 --> 15:32.436
(DOWN-TEMPO MUSIC PLAYING)

15:32.437 --> 15:33.637
Thank you.

15:42.303 --> 15:43.436
Thank you for coming.

15:43.437 --> 15:44.469
Father.

15:44.470 --> 15:46.670
- A brandy?
- Please.

15:53.871 --> 15:54.970
How's Grandmother?

15:55.871 --> 15:57.637
Hoping to see you.

15:58.170 --> 15:59.703
I thought a visit under
the circumstances

15:59.704 --> 16:00.836
might do more harm than good.

16:00.837 --> 16:02.637
I understand.

16:03.903 --> 16:06.736
Your grandmother and I have no intention

16:06.737 --> 16:08.703
of judging either of you.

16:08.704 --> 16:11.970
However, we would like to comment.

16:12.970 --> 16:14.770
Of course.

16:14.771 --> 16:16.737
You seem to have given up rather easily.

16:17.504 --> 16:20.369
I gather the fault lies with Olivia?

16:20.370 --> 16:22.737
I bear a good portion of the blame.

16:23.570 --> 16:26.403
But you've put that part of your...

16:26.404 --> 16:28.170
yourself aside.

16:29.837 --> 16:31.070
Thank you.

16:35.370 --> 16:37.469
I left her vulnerable to other feelings.

16:37.470 --> 16:40.636
Well, surely there's
hope for reconciling.

16:40.637 --> 16:41.903
No.

16:47.303 --> 16:49.437
And what was said of Georgie?

16:52.771 --> 16:56.137
We'll discuss details when
our feelings are less raw.

16:56.637 --> 16:58.437
You didn't even canvass him?

16:59.337 --> 17:00.436
In due course.

17:00.437 --> 17:02.737
You baffle me sometimes.

17:03.237 --> 17:06.368
I assume Olivia accepts
she's not keeping him.

17:06.369 --> 17:07.902
She loves him.

17:07.903 --> 17:11.569
I will not see my grandson
raised by some painter

17:11.569 --> 17:14.935
and carried off to London
when that inevitably fails.

17:15.704 --> 17:17.736
The courts would never
award her custody anyway.

17:17.737 --> 17:19.002
We needn't start thinking about that.

17:19.002 --> 17:20.837
We will if necessary.

17:21.637 --> 17:25.737
I am happy to see them
together if she remains here.

17:29.237 --> 17:33.102
You be as cavalier as you
wish with your marriage,

17:33.103 --> 17:34.903
but not with Georgie.

17:36.303 --> 17:37.102
He's my son.

17:37.103 --> 17:39.035
He is my grandson.

17:39.036 --> 17:40.469
He is a Bligh.

17:40.470 --> 17:42.536
He will be raised by us.

17:42.537 --> 17:44.437
Grow a backbone, man!

17:49.871 --> 17:52.035
CAROLYN: It's not a message
I enjoy delivering.

17:52.036 --> 17:53.302
(BABY COOING)

17:53.303 --> 17:55.969
But at least it avoids any
possible unpleasantness

17:55.970 --> 17:57.036
between you and George.

18:00.036 --> 18:02.636
Has James summoned the nerve

18:02.637 --> 18:05.771
to tell you he's exploring
his own desires?

18:07.837 --> 18:10.369
So where is Georgie better placed,

18:10.370 --> 18:14.537
with me or peering out of the
crib at James and Henry Fox?

18:16.437 --> 18:18.370
Is that the truth?

18:18.903 --> 18:21.970
I left when I found them together.

18:23.404 --> 18:25.804
It's why he's capitulated so easily.

18:26.370 --> 18:28.569
(SIGHS)

18:28.570 --> 18:31.737
Well, don't tell George,
please, if James doesn't.

18:32.637 --> 18:37.002
In other words, bear all the
shame and part with my son?

18:37.003 --> 18:40.102
That is truly a Bligh solution.

18:40.103 --> 18:42.604
The family takes the shame.

18:43.370 --> 18:46.036
James will be snapped in an
arranged adulterous tryst.

18:46.771 --> 18:48.703
The divorce will be
granted on those grounds,

18:48.704 --> 18:51.404
and you will receive a
generous settlement.

18:52.537 --> 18:56.370
You will be free to move
on to any life you choose.

18:57.437 --> 18:59.637
Without my baby.

19:04.003 --> 19:06.170
I'm afraid so.

19:11.003 --> 19:13.170
What if I fought for him?

19:13.871 --> 19:16.270
Then you would be named as adulteress.

19:18.837 --> 19:20.604
The courts will favor the family.

19:21.771 --> 19:23.437
I'm sorry.

19:28.437 --> 19:30.603
If you only knew.

19:30.604 --> 19:31.837
Knew what?

19:32.370 --> 19:35.504
I'll go before I say things I regret.

19:39.737 --> 19:42.437
(INSECTS CHIRPING)

19:53.170 --> 19:55.103
(PAPERS RUSTLING)

19:58.370 --> 19:59.570
ELIZABETH: Hello?

20:07.504 --> 20:12.103
And what's my prognosis,
in your opinion?

20:13.370 --> 20:15.170
I'm not your attending physician.

20:15.771 --> 20:18.237
But you <i>are</i> perusing my chart.

20:18.771 --> 20:20.703
And showing a good deal more interest

20:20.704 --> 20:23.370
than might be considered usual.

20:24.537 --> 20:27.170
So, your prognosis.

20:28.537 --> 20:30.369
A second attack of this nature

20:30.370 --> 20:32.935
doesn't augur well for longevity.

20:32.936 --> 20:35.669
(CHUCKLES) Thank you.

20:35.670 --> 20:37.303
You have a nice way with a euphemism.

20:39.036 --> 20:41.970
I assume that you're
reporting back to James.

20:43.737 --> 20:46.737
My body may be frail, but
my perceptions are not.

20:47.470 --> 20:53.070
I also assume that... the
attraction is mutual.

20:55.036 --> 20:57.170
(CLEARS THROAT) It is.

20:58.537 --> 21:00.503
Is that why Olivia left?

21:00.504 --> 21:02.036
Partly.

21:02.804 --> 21:04.370
I see.

21:05.537 --> 21:09.437
It... It was never my
intention to cause harm.

21:09.970 --> 21:11.903
Sit down, Mr. Fox.

21:15.370 --> 21:19.736
Should the seemingly
inevitable transpire,

21:19.737 --> 21:21.504
James will need a friend.

21:22.804 --> 21:25.836
I forced him to marry once.

21:25.837 --> 21:27.771
I shan't do it again.

21:30.303 --> 21:33.636
I count on you to teach him

21:33.637 --> 21:36.537
what I imagine you already know...

21:37.670 --> 21:43.070
how to be as you are
whilst avoiding scandal.

21:44.337 --> 21:47.704
I think that's the best we
can hope for now, isn't it?

21:53.036 --> 21:55.704
Gawping does not become you, Doctor.

21:59.470 --> 22:02.935
REGINA: I appreciate your keen
observations, Mrs. Collins.

22:02.936 --> 22:04.503
As wife of the member to be,

22:04.504 --> 22:06.170
there's only so much I can keep up with.

22:06.936 --> 22:09.236
Anything you could glean on
this new police sergeant,

22:09.237 --> 22:10.202
for instance.

22:10.203 --> 22:12.536
I hear he's rather charming.

22:12.537 --> 22:14.902
And I do hope people
aren't gossiping too much

22:14.903 --> 22:18.137
over this poor girl's suicide.

22:18.604 --> 22:20.969
DORIS: How lovely!

22:20.970 --> 22:26.136
A lady such as yourself offering
to help me with my little task.

22:26.137 --> 22:27.703
Oh, I'm glad to.

22:27.704 --> 22:29.369
(CHUCKLES)

22:29.370 --> 22:31.704
(BOTTLES CLANKING)

22:32.303 --> 22:34.871
I must go, I'm afraid.

22:35.337 --> 22:36.636
Good night.

22:36.637 --> 22:39.036
(DOWN-TEMPO MUSIC PLAYING)

22:48.170 --> 22:50.103
(CORK SQUEAKS)

23:16.370 --> 23:18.437
(MUSIC CONTINUES)

23:22.737 --> 23:25.436
I worked out what's been niggling at me.

23:25.437 --> 23:26.404
What's that?

23:27.737 --> 23:31.137
Well, all the children have
written how much she loved them.

23:33.103 --> 23:35.170
Milly was found in the classroom.

23:35.936 --> 23:38.871
She would never have let
them find her like that.

23:39.504 --> 23:41.036
She did, but.

23:42.036 --> 23:43.936
If she killed herself.

23:46.370 --> 23:48.170
What if she didn't?

23:51.303 --> 23:54.103
(INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS)

24:01.036 --> 24:03.102
I know what you're saying.

24:03.103 --> 24:05.102
There's only one problem, though.

24:05.103 --> 24:07.237
She hadn't an enemy in the world.

24:08.370 --> 24:09.536
Are you sure?

24:09.537 --> 24:11.770
No one who'd want to hurt her.

24:11.771 --> 24:12.569
No.

24:12.570 --> 24:15.737
She was... heartsore.

24:16.237 --> 24:17.936
I should have seen how bad.

24:19.137 --> 24:21.403
- Sorry. I didn't mean...
- It is best left there.

24:21.404 --> 24:22.936
I...

24:25.036 --> 24:26.969
All right. (CLAPS HANDS) Come on.

24:26.970 --> 24:29.303
Right there. Come on.

24:29.871 --> 24:31.936
(DOWN-TEMPO MUSIC PLAYS)

24:42.303 --> 24:44.436
What time is it?

24:44.437 --> 24:47.103
You countrymen are always
up with the larks.

24:48.170 --> 24:50.737
One of the benefits of being in town.

24:52.303 --> 24:54.703
How was your night shift?

24:54.704 --> 24:56.303
Interesting.

25:00.737 --> 25:03.036
Order us breakfast. I'm gonna shower.

25:11.570 --> 25:13.504
(DOORBELL RINGS)

25:14.237 --> 25:15.236
Coming.

25:15.237 --> 25:17.170
(WATER RUNNING)

25:18.936 --> 25:20.836
Good morning, sir.

25:20.837 --> 25:22.203
Put it over there.

25:33.936 --> 25:35.703
Breakfast for two, sir.

25:35.704 --> 25:37.870
I hope you enjoy it.

25:37.871 --> 25:39.936
(MUSIC CONTINUES)

25:43.337 --> 25:45.102
Presumptuous pup.

25:45.103 --> 25:46.369
(METAL CLANGS)

25:46.370 --> 25:48.436
I'm sure he imagined
some high-class floozy

25:48.437 --> 25:50.069
who serviced you mercilessly.

25:50.070 --> 25:52.437
It's not his place to imagine anything.

25:53.903 --> 25:55.970
I'm sure he's seen it all.

25:57.170 --> 25:58.504
Well, perhaps not all.

26:01.570 --> 26:04.136
I have a good mind to report
his smirk to the management.

26:04.137 --> 26:05.404
Lesson number one.

26:06.203 --> 26:09.803
When you've something to
hide, don't initiate a fuss.

26:09.804 --> 26:12.536
Quickest way to have questions
asked about your doings

26:12.537 --> 26:13.970
is to draw attention to them.

26:16.003 --> 26:17.437
You make it sound like school.

26:18.970 --> 26:21.103
With your grandmother's blessing.

26:22.103 --> 26:24.137
As I said, interesting night.

26:26.504 --> 26:28.002
I'm looking for Mrs. Bligh's room.

26:28.003 --> 26:30.169
Just at the end on the left.

26:30.170 --> 26:31.337
Thank you.

26:39.170 --> 26:41.103
(KNOCK ON DOOR)

26:42.036 --> 26:43.935
(EXHALES DEEPLY)

26:43.936 --> 26:45.670
At last.

26:49.637 --> 26:51.703
Oh, thank you.

26:51.704 --> 26:52.736
Um...

26:52.737 --> 26:54.771
Oh, they're beautiful.

26:57.537 --> 26:59.137
How are you feeling?

26:59.970 --> 27:01.704
Better by the day.

27:08.370 --> 27:11.203
Did Henry report our conversation?

27:15.504 --> 27:17.170
What made you see it?

27:19.103 --> 27:22.370
The increase in time spent away.

27:24.370 --> 27:26.804
The look in your eyes
when he's mentioned.

27:28.137 --> 27:32.370
Echoes of things I experienced
with your grandfather.

27:36.470 --> 27:38.369
It doesn't disgust you?

27:38.370 --> 27:40.302
(DOWN-TEMPO MUSIC PLAYS)

27:40.303 --> 27:46.437
I'll never truly understand
it, and I worry for you...

27:47.470 --> 27:50.703
but I know you won't be happy
with another sham marriage

27:50.704 --> 27:52.637
or with celibacy.

27:55.036 --> 27:58.504
Does my frankness shock you?

28:02.604 --> 28:04.370
Yes, it does.

28:08.704 --> 28:10.604
(MUSIC CONTINUES)

28:14.537 --> 28:16.437
I love you, Grandmother.

28:20.370 --> 28:23.036
It's a changing world, my darling.

28:24.036 --> 28:27.736
Let's see how many changes
I can accommodate.

28:27.737 --> 28:29.637
(CHUCKLES)

28:31.704 --> 28:33.136
Perhaps suggest that to Father.

28:33.137 --> 28:33.935
Oh!

28:33.936 --> 28:36.236
(BOTH LAUGH)

28:36.237 --> 28:38.236
- Bye!
- Publish or perish!

28:38.237 --> 28:40.804
- (WHISTLE BLOWS)
- (LAUGHS)

28:44.003 --> 28:45.936
How do you feel about it?

28:46.437 --> 28:47.569
The book.

28:47.570 --> 28:49.403
Oh, I'm trying to get
used to it, you know?

28:49.404 --> 28:51.002
She's changed it a bit.

28:51.003 --> 28:53.370
- Well, you're a good man.
- Well, sometimes.

28:54.370 --> 28:56.403
(SIGHS) Have I missed the train?

28:56.404 --> 28:58.569
Oh, it must have been early.

28:58.570 --> 29:01.002
Parcel for my husband.

29:01.003 --> 29:03.003
Wretched rail.

29:04.070 --> 29:06.270
It's good to see you, Jack.

29:07.070 --> 29:08.503
Regina!

29:08.504 --> 29:10.203
Excuse me. Regina!

29:12.237 --> 29:14.002
Could I have a word with you, please?

29:14.003 --> 29:15.169
Don't tell me.

29:15.170 --> 29:17.870
An opportunity for spousal gallantry.

29:17.871 --> 29:19.603
I'll say it for you.

29:19.604 --> 29:23.436
Do anything to upset Anna, and
you'll have me to deal with.

29:23.437 --> 29:24.603
And you will too.

29:24.604 --> 29:27.704
Anna is more than capable
of looking after herself.

29:28.303 --> 29:30.002
You forget I was the dirt-poor Italian

29:30.003 --> 29:32.202
who took on Mrs. Bligh and won.

29:32.203 --> 29:33.770
Your point?

29:33.771 --> 29:35.704
I can beat you too.

29:37.003 --> 29:39.770
It's a shame we're at odds.

29:39.771 --> 29:42.202
We've both fought for love, and...

29:42.203 --> 29:44.935
we're both ready to defend it.

29:44.936 --> 29:48.036
We'd make better friends
than enemies, Gino.

29:49.370 --> 29:51.569
We've got plenty of cows on the farm.

29:51.570 --> 29:53.770
We don't need any more.

29:53.771 --> 29:55.369
<i>Signorina.</i>

29:55.370 --> 29:57.570
(MID-TEMPO MUSIC PLAYS)

30:01.036 --> 30:02.771
Rose!

30:04.370 --> 30:05.803
Rose!

30:05.804 --> 30:07.737
(FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING)

30:08.970 --> 30:11.902
I bought a new lipstick the other day.

30:11.903 --> 30:15.137
I think it might suit you
far more than it suits me.

30:16.370 --> 30:17.537
Come here.

30:26.437 --> 30:28.771
(MUSIC CONTINUES)

30:44.103 --> 30:45.737
Lovely.

30:46.337 --> 30:48.370
See how pretty you are.

30:50.303 --> 30:51.770
Take it.

30:51.771 --> 30:52.969
I insist.

30:52.970 --> 30:55.170
Thank you, Mrs. Bligh.

30:57.303 --> 31:01.137
There's just one little thing
I need you to do for me.

31:01.871 --> 31:03.703
(KNOCKING)

31:03.704 --> 31:05.803
CAROLYN: Coming!

31:05.804 --> 31:08.036
(VEHICLES PASSING)

31:11.537 --> 31:12.503
(GASPS)

31:12.504 --> 31:13.970
Get out!

31:15.570 --> 31:16.370
Leave!

31:17.203 --> 31:18.935
- Now!
- Oh, calm down.

31:18.936 --> 31:19.902
Listen.

31:19.903 --> 31:22.935
I hear rumblings about
your nephew's marriage.

31:22.936 --> 31:25.369
I just want the good oil
before I tackle George.

31:25.370 --> 31:27.102
That is none of your affair!

31:27.103 --> 31:28.369
Relax.

31:28.370 --> 31:31.336
If your dubious virtue
was in any danger,

31:31.337 --> 31:34.369
you'd be on your back
already, moaning for more.

31:34.370 --> 31:36.669
- I...
- (BOTTLES CLANKING)

31:36.670 --> 31:37.902
just want confirmation.

31:37.903 --> 31:39.036
That's all.

31:41.737 --> 31:43.969
James and Olivia have separated.

31:43.970 --> 31:46.069
It is the family's business.

31:46.070 --> 31:47.703
There'll be no separation.

31:47.704 --> 31:49.369
You can't stop it.

31:49.370 --> 31:51.137
I can do what I want.

31:51.737 --> 31:53.036
You know that.

31:57.903 --> 31:59.302
(EXHALES DEEPLY)

31:59.303 --> 32:02.237
(BIRDS CHIRPING, COWS LOWING)

32:16.837 --> 32:18.803
Mr. Poletti.

32:18.804 --> 32:20.369
Rose.

32:20.370 --> 32:22.604
I brought something for you.

32:24.637 --> 32:26.035
It's dinner.

32:26.036 --> 32:27.803
I heard Mrs. Poletti's away.

32:27.804 --> 32:29.436
Thank you.

32:29.437 --> 32:30.736
Mrs. Bligh didn't...

32:30.737 --> 32:32.902
Mrs. Bligh doesn't know.

32:32.903 --> 32:35.170
Don't get yourself into trouble.

32:36.337 --> 32:38.536
You were kind to me...

32:38.537 --> 32:42.070
that night with the baby in the barn.

32:42.903 --> 32:44.436
It's a thank-you.

32:44.437 --> 32:46.170
It's fine.

32:46.704 --> 32:49.102
There's one other thing.

32:49.103 --> 32:53.436
I was wondering maybe, on my days off...

32:53.437 --> 32:54.836
could you teach me Italian?

32:54.837 --> 32:56.170
I could pay you.

32:57.036 --> 32:59.503
I want to go there one day... Rome.

32:59.504 --> 33:00.836
Really? Roma?

33:00.837 --> 33:02.936
You can dream, can't you?

33:04.804 --> 33:05.969
Okay.

33:05.970 --> 33:07.569
Thank you.

33:07.570 --> 33:09.002
And, uh, no charge.

33:09.003 --> 33:10.369
- Oh, but I can...
- No, no, no, no.

33:10.370 --> 33:12.035
That's the deal.

33:12.036 --> 33:14.369
Maybe I could find you a good
Italian husband in the bargain.

33:14.370 --> 33:15.504
Maybe you can.

33:16.804 --> 33:19.636
I don't care how you manage
it, but until the election

33:19.637 --> 33:22.102
and for a good few months
after, happy families.

33:22.103 --> 33:24.836
They're not my choices to...

33:24.837 --> 33:26.436
to make.

33:26.437 --> 33:30.136
I don't want a messy Bligh
divorce all over the newspapers

33:30.137 --> 33:31.636
as you're coming into the home stretch.

33:31.637 --> 33:32.302
Fix it.

33:32.303 --> 33:34.870
I would prefer a change of tone.

33:34.871 --> 33:37.369
Don't be so bloody sensitive.

33:37.370 --> 33:39.669
(MID-TEMPO MUSIC PLAYS)

33:39.670 --> 33:41.436
It's good practice for Parliament.

33:41.437 --> 33:43.337
(CHUCKLES)

33:46.871 --> 33:49.370
(INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS)

34:00.903 --> 34:02.736
You're not going out to play?

34:02.737 --> 34:04.771
(SNIFFLES)

34:05.903 --> 34:07.637
What is it?

34:13.771 --> 34:17.101
You didn't write anything
yesterday about Miss Davis.

34:17.103 --> 34:19.002
(EXHALES DEEPLY)

34:19.003 --> 34:21.370
We can talk about it if you like.

34:22.969 --> 34:25.034
It's all right. It's all right.

34:25.036 --> 34:26.202
It's gonna be all right.

34:26.203 --> 34:28.369
It's not, Miss. It's not!

34:28.370 --> 34:30.302
I killed her!

34:30.303 --> 34:33.103
(BREATHING HEAVILY, WHEEZING)

34:34.936 --> 34:36.436
It's all right, Emma.

34:36.437 --> 34:38.703
Just breathe deeply.

34:38.704 --> 34:41.469
(BIRDS CHIRPING)

34:41.469 --> 34:43.871
(TELEPHONE RINGING)

34:55.437 --> 34:57.336
I've given her something for the asthma.

34:57.337 --> 34:59.902
Well, even if it just helps her sleep.

34:59.903 --> 35:01.836
S-She hasn't been.

35:01.837 --> 35:05.237
Have you any idea why she
might feel responsible?

35:06.370 --> 35:10.369
She came home cross the day
they found Miss Davis.

35:10.370 --> 35:11.636
She'd been kept in,

35:11.637 --> 35:13.603
and it meant she couldn't
go to a birthday party.

35:13.604 --> 35:15.202
(SIGHS)

35:15.203 --> 35:16.970
Other than that...

35:18.237 --> 35:23.236
When she heard, she
went pale as a ghost.

35:23.237 --> 35:25.003
I just thought she was sad.

35:26.804 --> 35:27.771
You can go in.

35:28.370 --> 35:30.170
Oh. Thank you, Doctor.

35:38.871 --> 35:40.871
I should get back.

35:41.537 --> 35:43.137
Um...

35:43.837 --> 35:45.437
Are you gonna call the police?

35:46.537 --> 35:47.969
Not yet.

35:47.970 --> 35:49.636
The new sergeant's pretty gung-ho.

35:49.637 --> 35:51.537
Better she doesn't wake up to that.

35:52.637 --> 35:55.504
(DOWN-TEMPO MUSIC PLAYS)

35:58.504 --> 36:01.703
(KNOCK ON DOOR)

36:01.704 --> 36:03.703
ANNA: Hello?

36:03.704 --> 36:04.803
It's me!

36:04.804 --> 36:06.970
Oh, my darling!

36:14.903 --> 36:17.569
Oh! Opening night of the Ice Capades.

36:17.570 --> 36:19.369
Those skaters know how to put it away.

36:19.370 --> 36:21.935
I'll just drop this and run.
Otherwise I'll be late.

36:21.936 --> 36:23.636
Wish me luck.

36:23.637 --> 36:25.102
I'm sure they love what you've written

36:25.103 --> 36:27.002
- or they wouldn't be seeing you.
- I hope.

36:27.003 --> 36:28.603
- Go! We'll talk later.
- Yes. (LAUGHS)

36:28.604 --> 36:29.737
Fingers crossed.

36:38.437 --> 36:40.470
(VOICE BREAKING) Oh, God.

36:42.903 --> 36:45.070
(TELEPHONE RINGING)

36:48.303 --> 36:49.770
Dr. Duncan.

36:49.771 --> 36:52.736
CAROLYN: It's me. Uh, Anna's arrived.

36:52.737 --> 36:53.935
I was wondering...

36:53.936 --> 36:57.569
I know I should be here for
her and Mother, but...

36:57.570 --> 36:58.871
I'm missing you.

36:59.936 --> 37:01.771
What do you think about my coming down?

37:02.437 --> 37:04.169
Mother will understand, don't you think?

37:04.170 --> 37:05.369
Should I?

37:05.370 --> 37:06.370
Are you all right?

37:06.970 --> 37:08.369
Of course.

37:08.370 --> 37:12.504
I'm just nervous about
letting Mother down.

37:13.637 --> 37:14.803
Excuse me, Doctor.

37:14.804 --> 37:16.403
Emma's awake. I think you should come.

37:16.404 --> 37:17.637
Yeah.

37:19.537 --> 37:21.137
Uh...

37:21.970 --> 37:24.703
Look, get here as soon as you can.

37:24.704 --> 37:26.137
I love you.

37:28.704 --> 37:30.771
(DIAL TONE)

37:32.103 --> 37:36.837
Evidently, Doctor, the poor
little thing got it all wrong.

37:37.303 --> 37:38.737
Thank you.

37:40.470 --> 37:43.969
(WHISPERING) Soon here, we're
gonna find out what it is.

37:43.970 --> 37:47.770
She thinks 'cause she said, "I
hope you die," to Miss Davis

37:47.771 --> 37:50.770
that she wished it on
her and made it happen.

37:50.771 --> 37:52.703
You silly duffer.

37:52.704 --> 37:54.302
Oh, sweetie.

37:54.303 --> 37:55.970
You mind if I, um...

37:59.637 --> 38:01.303
Emma...

38:02.570 --> 38:05.804
no one's... no one's
thoughts can make somebody die.

38:06.370 --> 38:07.603
In books, maybe.

38:07.604 --> 38:09.504
Not in the real world.

38:10.170 --> 38:11.771
I'm a doctor. I know.

38:12.370 --> 38:14.703
They said she was unhappy.

38:14.704 --> 38:16.169
She wasn't, but.

38:16.170 --> 38:17.369
Miss Davis?

38:17.370 --> 38:19.035
She was real happy.

38:19.036 --> 38:21.169
She died because I wished it upon her.

38:21.170 --> 38:22.636
JACK: (SIGHS)

38:22.637 --> 38:24.836
How do you know she was happy?

38:24.837 --> 38:25.837
The letter.

38:26.771 --> 38:27.836
What letter?

38:27.837 --> 38:30.704
The one that she opened
when she was keeping me in.

38:32.504 --> 38:35.370
(MID-TEMPO MUSIC PLAYING)

38:36.704 --> 38:39.404
(VEHICLE APPROACHING)

38:42.903 --> 38:45.437
(DOOR CLOSES)

38:45.970 --> 38:48.202
Kids. Here you go.

38:48.203 --> 38:49.804
That's a boy.

38:50.936 --> 38:53.804
(INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS)

39:03.637 --> 39:05.436
What did Emma say?

39:05.437 --> 39:06.669
It's very strange.

39:06.670 --> 39:09.504
She reckons Milly Davis
opened a letter that...

39:10.871 --> 39:13.903
Sergeant, this is Mrs. Nordmann.

39:14.437 --> 39:15.669
Nordmann?

39:15.670 --> 39:18.870
Yes. I've heard about you.

39:18.871 --> 39:20.436
We have a search to do.

39:20.437 --> 39:21.902
Would you mind stepping outside, please?

39:21.903 --> 39:24.269
Sergeant, all Milly's things
I sent to the family.

39:24.270 --> 39:26.202
Actually, I found a letter.

39:26.203 --> 39:28.902
It was slipped inside
the detention book,

39:28.903 --> 39:30.503
addressed to Milly.

39:30.504 --> 39:32.103
It's...

39:36.137 --> 39:37.102
Oh.

39:37.103 --> 39:38.136
The...

39:38.137 --> 39:40.970
The engagement was back on.

39:41.504 --> 39:43.102
Perhaps you're right.

39:43.103 --> 39:45.203
She said someone probably did it.

39:45.804 --> 39:46.935
Did you, now?

39:46.936 --> 39:49.202
Well, I just couldn't see
Milly risking the children

39:49.203 --> 39:50.503
finding her like that.

39:50.504 --> 39:52.403
It makes sense if you think about it.

39:52.404 --> 39:54.969
You're a real Miss Marple, aren't you?

39:54.970 --> 39:56.936
I'm just trying to help.

39:57.903 --> 39:58.903
Yeah.

40:02.370 --> 40:03.504
Miss Griggs.

40:04.036 --> 40:06.737
It seems you have an
issue with me, Sergeant.

40:11.137 --> 40:13.969
Your husband shot George Bligh, right?

40:13.970 --> 40:16.370
- I don't see what that...
- It's all right, Jack.

40:17.437 --> 40:19.370
That was proven to be an accident.

40:20.036 --> 40:23.170
And this was a suicide...
until it wasn't.

40:23.637 --> 40:25.804
I hear you're a Communist, too.

40:26.437 --> 40:28.370
I've got a few issues
with you, actually.

40:29.170 --> 40:30.337
But they'll keep.

40:32.070 --> 40:33.704
Constable.

40:39.036 --> 40:42.035
(TYPEWRITERS CLICKING)

40:42.036 --> 40:44.136
So, Miss Bligh...

40:44.137 --> 40:46.302
Oh, please, call me Anna.

40:46.303 --> 40:50.469
Well... I'm Mr. Cowan.

40:50.470 --> 40:53.369
As your editor,

40:53.370 --> 40:57.436
I shall be wanting to maintain
a professional distance.

40:57.437 --> 40:59.336
Are you saying that...

40:59.337 --> 41:01.636
I have no doubt we'll be publishing you.

41:01.637 --> 41:04.369
You're a very talented young woman.

41:04.370 --> 41:06.503
Thank you. I just...

41:06.504 --> 41:09.236
I'm so glad that you like my story.

41:09.237 --> 41:11.169
Ah. Well, yes.

41:11.170 --> 41:12.603
Your story.

41:12.604 --> 41:15.003
That's another matter.

41:15.570 --> 41:17.736
Oh, I'm sorry. I don't understand.

41:17.737 --> 41:21.369
Your manuscript proves you can write.

41:21.370 --> 41:24.137
Your subject matter, however...

41:24.837 --> 41:28.570
Readers aren't interested
in the dago experience.

41:29.303 --> 41:30.537
I beg your pardon.

41:33.903 --> 41:37.302
"Tender Vines," the story
of a wealthy young woman

41:37.303 --> 41:41.302
forgoing privilege to
marry an Italian farmer.

41:41.303 --> 41:45.069
It strains credulity as well
as readers' sympathies.

41:45.070 --> 41:48.070
Mr. Cowan, that's my own story.

41:48.704 --> 41:51.336
You are a lady,

41:51.337 --> 41:53.837
a member of Australia's squattocracy.

41:54.903 --> 41:59.436
I have a contract here for
a different work entirely,

41:59.437 --> 42:05.969
to be written about your world
by someone who's lived in it.

42:05.970 --> 42:09.403
There's a signing fee and
guaranteed publication.

42:09.404 --> 42:12.370
You could be the next
Henry Handel Richardson.

42:13.771 --> 42:16.002
It's a generous offer.

42:16.003 --> 42:18.136
But, of course, if you
wish to seek advice...

42:18.137 --> 42:20.569
You're not interested
in what I've written.

42:20.570 --> 42:23.102
Your talent, yes.

42:23.103 --> 42:26.036
Your subject matter, no.

42:26.637 --> 42:28.703
You must remember it
wasn't that long ago

42:28.704 --> 42:31.303
we were fighting the dagos.

42:31.771 --> 42:33.136
Dagos.

42:33.137 --> 42:35.469
That's my husband you're talking about.

42:35.470 --> 42:37.770
No need to take offense.
It's just a word.

42:37.771 --> 42:39.035
Well, here are some words.

42:39.036 --> 42:40.736
And they're just words... dago words.

42:40.737 --> 42:42.069
<i>Va fangool.</i>

42:42.070 --> 42:44.536
Translate that and see what a lady I am.

42:44.537 --> 42:46.136
(MID-TEMPO MUSIC PLAYS)

42:46.137 --> 42:47.703
(DOOR OPENS)

42:47.704 --> 42:49.936
(BIRDS CHIRPING)

42:57.837 --> 42:59.337
Rose!

43:01.303 --> 43:04.636
I trust Gino appreciated our gesture.

43:04.637 --> 43:07.102
He's taught me a few words already.

43:07.103 --> 43:08.969
<i>Buon giorno. Come sta?</i>

43:08.970 --> 43:11.969
It means, "Good morning. How are you?"

43:11.970 --> 43:14.604
You'll be quite the Italiana
before you're done.

43:18.137 --> 43:20.771
(MUSIC CONTINUES)

43:21.370 --> 43:25.703
I suppose you think
me a scandalous fool.

43:25.704 --> 43:27.035
Well, perhaps less so,

43:27.036 --> 43:29.736
not having had what you
said to him translated.

43:29.737 --> 43:31.069
Best not.

43:31.070 --> 43:32.137
Trust me.

43:33.370 --> 43:35.370
Well, there are other publishers.

43:36.670 --> 43:38.870
Perhaps Sir Richard might
advise on the way forward.

43:38.871 --> 43:39.670
No.

43:40.337 --> 43:43.103
His connections to
publishing are tenuous.

43:43.903 --> 43:46.503
He owns newspapers.

43:46.504 --> 43:49.302
Anna would rather succeed on
her own merits, wouldn't you?

43:49.303 --> 43:50.536
I hope to, but if Sir...

43:50.537 --> 43:52.337
There. Good.

43:53.570 --> 43:55.036
Is anything wrong?

43:57.103 --> 43:59.903
I'm simply missing Jack.

44:01.771 --> 44:04.703
I hope neither of you mind
if I head back to Inverness,

44:04.704 --> 44:06.936
see if the campaign needs a hand.

44:08.537 --> 44:10.203
(BABY WHINES, CRIES)

44:12.003 --> 44:15.102
You know what I really can't resolve?

44:15.103 --> 44:18.569
Not one of them has taken
my feelings into account.

44:18.570 --> 44:20.935
A decision is made, and
it's a fait accompli!

44:20.936 --> 44:24.202
- Okay. Okay.
- It is just so damned unfair!

44:24.203 --> 44:25.935
After all that I have suffered for them,

44:25.936 --> 44:27.035
they think they can just...

44:27.036 --> 44:29.870
Look, you have to admit he
<i>would</i> be well looked after.

44:29.871 --> 44:32.169
Ash Park, a nanny, his father.

44:32.170 --> 44:34.302
This isn't a decision they can make.

44:34.303 --> 44:35.935
Darling, I think they can.

44:35.936 --> 44:37.303
No.

44:40.936 --> 44:43.771
It's an unpalatable truth.

44:47.670 --> 44:49.303
Truth?

44:51.537 --> 44:54.437
We'd all buckle under
the weight of that.

44:55.837 --> 44:57.103
Me most of all.

45:00.771 --> 45:03.036
You want the truth?

45:07.637 --> 45:10.603
James isn't Georgie's father.

45:10.604 --> 45:11.736
But you said...

45:11.737 --> 45:13.804
I didn't give birth to him.

45:15.604 --> 45:17.770
(INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS)

45:17.771 --> 45:20.935
After my first attack, I interfered,

45:20.936 --> 45:25.436
to try to force my values, my
increasingly outmoded values,

45:25.437 --> 45:26.935
on you all.

45:26.936 --> 45:29.103
My motive was love.

45:29.537 --> 45:31.069
The outcome was unfortunate.

45:31.070 --> 45:33.102
So this time, I...

45:33.103 --> 45:37.436
I want to use my reprieve
to see you all happy...

45:37.437 --> 45:39.437
happily yourselves.

45:40.036 --> 45:41.902
I like this new grandmother.

45:41.903 --> 45:44.569
Mm. I do too, rather.

45:44.570 --> 45:46.102
And what about you?

45:46.103 --> 45:47.136
Mr. Goddard?

45:47.137 --> 45:50.069
No. With my prognosis, no.

45:50.070 --> 45:52.836
- Well, shouldn't you at least...
- No. He thinks I rejected him.

45:52.837 --> 45:54.870
Best left that way.

45:54.871 --> 45:56.302
Oh.

45:56.303 --> 45:57.770
Now, you know,

45:57.771 --> 46:00.536
I think your mother was
wrong about Sir Richard.

46:00.537 --> 46:03.369
Will you fetch me my book?
It's in my top drawer there.

46:03.370 --> 46:05.369
I thought you weren't interfering.

46:05.370 --> 46:07.969
(EXHALES DEEPLY) Only to the good.

46:07.970 --> 46:09.404
Mm-hmm.

46:10.604 --> 46:12.437
Ah, yes.

46:14.936 --> 46:18.504
You're not... shocked?

46:21.804 --> 46:23.136
I am unshockable.

46:23.137 --> 46:25.537
(CHUCKLES)

46:26.003 --> 46:30.069
James was in no position
to deal with a stillborn.

46:30.070 --> 46:32.569
You <i>can</i> see, I...

46:32.570 --> 46:36.503
I did it... for love.

46:36.504 --> 46:38.303
<i>I</i> understand.

46:38.903 --> 46:40.336
But they may not.

46:40.337 --> 46:44.303
Your actions were outrageous, Olivia.

46:44.771 --> 46:48.936
There was a sense to them at the time.

46:51.637 --> 46:53.636
Perhaps less so now.

46:53.637 --> 46:54.871
Mm.

46:56.771 --> 46:58.437
Lloyd?

46:59.370 --> 47:04.736
If I told them the truth... it
would guarantee me Georgie.

47:04.737 --> 47:06.603
Um, not necessarily.

47:06.604 --> 47:08.935
George would only go to court for blood.

47:08.936 --> 47:11.369
- He wouldn't fight for him.
- But James might.

47:11.370 --> 47:13.504
James has what he wants.

47:15.237 --> 47:17.370
James has his man.

47:23.404 --> 47:26.370
This is not who I am.

47:29.737 --> 47:31.670
(SIGHS)

47:34.103 --> 47:35.871
So what now?

47:41.070 --> 47:42.670
The truth.

47:45.970 --> 47:49.137
For the right reason.

47:52.470 --> 47:54.303
For our solution.

47:58.871 --> 48:00.935
He had his back up as soon
as he heard your name.

48:00.936 --> 48:03.369
Franklin clearly got in
his ear before he left.

48:03.370 --> 48:05.637
- You all right, then?
- I've handled worse.

48:06.203 --> 48:07.803
- Ruddy Doris.
- Hmm?

48:07.804 --> 48:10.203
You were done with your
library card hours ago.

48:10.771 --> 48:13.236
There are many ways
to be useful, Doctor.

48:13.237 --> 48:15.236
Yeah. Well, sniffing for
gossip isn't one of them.

48:15.237 --> 48:16.902
Scoot.

48:16.903 --> 48:20.569
Dr. Duncan can be so
abrasive in a crisis.

48:20.570 --> 48:22.969
An eventful day at school, I hear.

48:22.970 --> 48:26.002
It's given me a lot of
respect for teachers.

48:26.003 --> 48:29.970
I might pop by Ash Park
before heading home.

48:30.437 --> 48:32.935
After a somewhat hesitant start,

48:32.936 --> 48:36.369
the news Mrs. Bligh and I have
formed a charming intimacy.

48:36.370 --> 48:38.035
She's asked to be kept informed.

48:38.036 --> 48:39.137
Of what?

48:39.704 --> 48:42.770
Of Milly's death, the
new police sergeant,

48:42.771 --> 48:44.002
what's being said.

48:44.003 --> 48:45.770
Did she know her?

48:45.771 --> 48:49.771
As Mrs. Bligh, her interests
are in all things Inverness.

48:50.370 --> 48:53.436
Imagine my thrill the other
day when she visited me

48:53.437 --> 48:56.637
and even stayed to help
me with my little tasks.

48:57.804 --> 48:58.771
Which day?

49:00.637 --> 49:03.704
(DOWN-TEMPO MUSIC PLAYING)

49:12.871 --> 49:15.603
DORIS: All the herbs are
from my own garden.

49:15.604 --> 49:18.202
The chamomile and the red raspberry leaf

49:18.203 --> 49:21.469
are especially good for low spirits

49:21.470 --> 49:22.770
or those who are carrying.

49:22.771 --> 49:25.503
Mrs. Nordmann was telling
me how much she values it.

49:25.504 --> 49:27.503
Oh, indeed, indeed.

49:27.504 --> 49:29.102
If I could be so bold,

49:29.103 --> 49:31.569
perhaps more of that delicious cake?

49:31.570 --> 49:34.103
Oh! Of course!

49:34.604 --> 49:36.035
I won't be a moment.

49:36.036 --> 49:38.137
- I'm in no hurry.
- Mm.

49:56.737 --> 49:58.737
Here we are!

49:59.604 --> 50:01.569
Oh, isn't this cozy?

50:01.570 --> 50:02.903
REGINA: Most.

50:11.604 --> 50:13.804
(INSECTS CHIRPING)

50:17.370 --> 50:19.369
Thought I'd get started on the tucker.

50:19.370 --> 50:21.237
Chops and mash do?

50:44.036 --> 50:46.669
Roy, can I borrow your truck?

50:46.670 --> 50:47.836
Suppose so.

50:47.837 --> 50:50.102
I don't know how long I'll be.

50:50.103 --> 50:51.669
Something wrong?

50:51.670 --> 50:53.303
You all right, missy?

50:56.903 --> 50:59.970
(UP-TEMPO MUSIC PLAYING)

51:17.370 --> 51:19.236
- Excuse me, ma'am.
- Yes, Rose?

51:19.237 --> 51:20.536
Mrs. Nordmann's here.

51:20.537 --> 51:22.137
She asked for you.

51:23.903 --> 51:25.504
Send her in.

51:26.203 --> 51:27.370
I won't require you.

51:40.170 --> 51:42.771
To what do I owe this displeasure?

51:43.637 --> 51:45.437
I'm curious.

51:46.370 --> 51:48.303
How does it feel to be a murderer?

